NAME 
    find-replace
     
DESCRIPTION
    Replaces some characters with other characters in a string.
    
    This function requires three parameters...
        @1 = original string
        @2 = find string
        @3 = replace string

SYNOPSIS
    find-replace [STRING] [FIND] [REPLACE]
     
EXAMPLES
    echo $(find-replace "original_string" "original" "new")
        ~ (result is "new_string")
     
AVAILABLE OPTIONS:
    N/A